				<li id="16606155" class="cmnt-root" data="137" data-d="1649425081000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579785/Malenia's-Great-Rune" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">08 Apr 2022 09:38</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16606155" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I&apos;ve done a lot of testing, using mods and what not and i can guarantee you this is THE worst Great Rune in the entire game.<br/><br/><br/>1. This rune reduced your Flask healing, not 25% but 30%.<br/><br/>2. This is a &quot;Ninja debuff&quot; since it doesn&apos;t tell you in the description nor in game buff/debuff icon. This rune reduced Healing Effectiveness by 30%, just like Flask healing. What does this mean ? Well, basically all healing outside of Flask healing will be reduced (e.g Incant healing, Blessed Dew Talisman, etc.) In my opinion, this one is not a bug at all but rather intentional. Maybe FromSoft forgot to disclose it in the description of this Great Rune. The reason i think it&apos;s not a bug but rather intentional because if it&apos;s a bug, it must have something to do with game codes but in this case, you can literally tweak how much you want your Healing Effectiveness to increase or decrease.<br/><br/>3. The healing you get from immediately attack after taking damage determined by what type of weapon you use instead of damage you&apos;re doing. I&apos;ve a modded dagger with 10k damage for testing vs unmodded, no upgrade Maliketh&apos;s Black Blade and Maliketh&apos;s Black Blade healed me more than dagger with 10k damage. I don&apos;t understand FromSoft, i really don&apos;t.<br/><br/>4. You get this rune in the hardest area in the entire game. And to add insult to injury, all Great Runes will be removed in each NG+. So you don&apos;t really get to experiment this rune. And why should you ? It&apos;s bad, don&apos;t bother.<br/><br/>Long story short, this Great Rune sucks, don&apos;t bother. Save your Rune Arc on other Great Rune instead.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16606155" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16606155" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">5</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>142</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>5</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16606155"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16606155" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16606155"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
