				<li id="16597718" class="cmnt-root" data="58" data-d="1649236767000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579785/Malenia's-Great-Rune" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">06 Apr 2022 05:19</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16597718" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Not to repeat what everyone else has said, but this rune just doesn&apos;t really work in Elden Ring due to the fundamental building blocks of combat. Assuming you try to mirror Bloodborne by going with a low weight, fast swinging weapon (such as Malenia&apos;s Katanna) with light armor, using the rune to minimize damage taken when your dodging skills falter, you realize that you don&apos;t recover from damage as quickly as you do in Bloodborne, so the window to regain is lower. Another important aspect is that your natural dodge is longer than Bloodborne&apos;s quickstep, meaning that you can&apos;t just dodge the swing and still hit them within the window. <br/><br/>So maybe you try to game the system a bit, making so that instead of emulating blood borne, you go big and try to just poise your way through hits and use the rune to heal up damage you take. I remember going full Havel&apos;s in DS1, just swinging around a big number and daring the opponent to stop me. The issue with that is, well, a lot of the end game bosses are both mobile and heavy on damage. A heavy hitter trying to trade blows with a specific boss that wields a black-blade will not succeed. <br/><br/>The final nail in the coffin is that you get it, at the earliest, with about 5 mainline story bosses left. You will likely spend 80% to 99% of the game without this rune available to you, so you have to play the overwhelming majority of the game without the core component to a Bloodborne play style. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16597718" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16597718" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>58</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16597718"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16597718" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16597718"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
